This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect personal information obtained from participants attending our workshop. We respect your privacy and are committed to safeguarding your personal data. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your personal information.

1. Information We Collect:

1.1. Registration Information: When you register for our workshop, we may collect your name, contact details (such as email address, phone number), and any additional information required for workshop registration.

1.2. Payment Information: If applicable, we may collect payment information necessary to process workshop registration fees or other charges. However, we do not store your payment details. All payments are securely processed by our third-party payment service providers.

1.3. Workshop Interaction: During the workshop, we may collect information related to your participation, including questions, comments, or feedback you provide during discussions or activities.

1. Use of Information:

2.1. Workshop Administration: We use the information collected to facilitate workshop registration, confirm attendance, and communicate workshop-related updates, materials, or changes.

2.2. Workshop Improvement: We may analyze participant information to improve our workshops, customize content, and enhance the learning experience.

2.3. Communication: We may use your contact information to respond to your inquiries, provide support, or send administrative notifications regarding the workshop.

2.4. Legal Compliance: In exceptional circumstances, we may use or disclose your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or government requests.

1. Data Sharing and Disclosure:

3.1. Third-Party Service Providers: We may share your personal information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in delivering the workshop, such as registration management, email communication, or payment processing. These service providers are contractually obligated to protect your information and use it solely for the specified purposes.

3.2. Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law or if we believe that such disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, comply with a judicial proceeding, court order, or legal process.

1. Data Retention:

We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

1. Security Measures:

We take reasonable measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, loss, misuse, alteration, or destruction. However, no data transmission or storage system can guarantee absolute security. Please note that you provide your information at your own risk.

1. Your Rights:

You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information, subject to applicable laws. If you would like to exercise these rights or have any questions about your personal information, please contact us using the provided contact details.

1. Updates to this Privacy Policy:

We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be effective upon posting the revised policy on our website. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates.

1. Contact Us:

If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact us using the following information:

Alejandro Muro, +34 66 16 08 693

Thank you for participating in our workshop and entrusting us with your personal information.
